revision.text:
The '''1991 population census in Croatia''' was the last [[census]] of the population of [[Croatia]] taken before the [[Croatian War of Independence]]. It was conducted by the [[Croatian Bureau of Statistics]] during the final week of March 1991. For the 1991 census there were 106 municipalities of which five were part of [[Zagreb]].
==Population by ethnicity==
*'''TOTAL = 4,784,265 ''' *[[Croats]] = 3,736,356 (78.1%) *[[Serbs of Croatia|Serbs]] = 581,663 (12.2%) *[[Yugoslavs in Croatia|Yugoslavs]] = 106,041 (2.2%) *[[Muslims by nationality|Muslims]] = 43,469 (0.9%) *[[Slovenes of Croatia|Slovenes]] = 22,376 (0.5%) *[[Hungarians of Croatia|Hungarians]] = 22,355 (0.5%) *[[Italians of Croatia|Italians]] = 21,303 (0.4%) *[[Czechs of Croatia|Czechs]] = 13,086 (0.3%) *[[Albanians of Croatia|Albanians]] = 12,032 (0.3%) *[[Montenegrins of Croatia|Montenegrins]] = 9,724 (0.2%) *[[Romani people of Croatia|Romani]] = 6,695 (0.1%) *[[Macedonians of Croatia|Macedonians]] = 6,280 (0.1%) *[[Slovaks of Croatia|Slovaks]] = 6,606 (0.1%) *[[Rusyns of Croatia|Rusyns]] 3,253 (0.1%) *[[Germans of Croatia|Germans]] = 2,635 (0.1%) *[[Ukrainians of Croatia|Ukrainians]] = 2,494 *[[Romanians of Croatia|Romanians]] = 810 *[[Russians of Croatia|Russians]] = 706 *[[Poles of Croatia|Poles]] = 679 *[[Jews of Croatia|Jews]] = 600 *[[Bulgarians of Croatia|Bulgarians]] = 458 *[[Turks in Croatia|Turks]] = 320 *[[Greeks of Croatia|Greeks]] = 281 *[[Austrians of Croatia|Austrians]] = 214 *[[Morlachs of Croatia|Morlachs]] = 22 *''others'' = 3,012 *''unspecified'' = 73,376 *''regional affiliation'' = 45,493 *''unknown'' = 62,926
