{{Infobox ethnic group |group = Iranians in Lebanon |image = |population = '''4,000'''<ref name="mmedia.me">{{cite web|url=https://now.mmedia.me/lb/en/reportsfeatures/little_iran_in_lebanon_|title=Little Iran in Lebanon?|date=5 January 2010|publisher=|accessdate=8 February 2015}}</ref> - '''5,000'''<ref name="aawsat.net">{{cite web|url=http://www.aawsat.net/2008/07/article55258200|title=Iranians in Lebanon: Between History and Politics|work=ASHARQ AL-AWSAT|accessdate=8 February 2015}}</ref> |date= |url= |title= |accessdate= |popplace = [[Beirut]], [[Nabatieh]] |langs = [[Persian language|Persian]], [[Kurdish language|Kurdish]], and [[Arabic language|Arabic]] |rels = Predominantly [[Islam]], minority [[Christianity]] |related = [[Iranian peoples|Iranians]], [[Arab]]s, [[Azerbaijani people|Azeris]], [[Armenians]], [[Lebanese people|Lebanese]], [[Turkish people|Turks]]<!-- DON'T REMOVE MINORITY ETHNIC GROUPS --> }}
'''Iranians in Lebanon''' are people of [[Iran]]ian background or descent residing in [[Lebanon]]. Some of them are Lebanese citizens while some are migrants or descendants born in Lebanon with Iranian heritage. Many Iranians in Lebanon live in [[Nabatieh]]. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailystar.com.lb/News/Politics/2013/Jun-14/220374-iranians-in-lebanon-vote-for-new-president.ashx#axzz30DsG6nNq|title=Iranians in Lebanon vote for new president|work=The Daily Star Newspaper - Lebanon|accessdate=8 February 2015}}</ref> Many of the Iranians in Lebanon are carpet traders. <ref name="aawsat.net"/><ref name="mmedia.me"/>
==Notable people== * [[Musa al-Sadr]] - Iranian born of Lebanese descent
